snippet.title: 2014 Bentley Continental GT V8 S

snippet.title: 2012 Bentley Continental GT
snippet.description: The 2012 Bentley Continental GT makes for an excellent music-listening room while cruising down the highway or back roads, but tech-focused drivers will find the cabin electronics subpar for the car's class.

snippet.title: 2014 Bentley Continental GT Speed Convertible
snippet.description: The new Bentley Continental GT Speed Convertible pulls out all the stops when it comes to performance and luxury, but falls short of the cabin tech cutting edge.

snippet.title: 2013 Ford Mustang GT Premium
snippet.description: The 2013 Ford Mustang GT looks very cool and churns out tons of power, yet its reasonable fuel economy, easy driving manners, and useful cabin tech make it a fun daily driver.

snippet.title: David Brown Automotive Speedback GT: Vintage look, modern foundation
snippet.description: David Brown loves classic cars -- the look, style and speed appeals. The reliability does not. So he's decided to make a car that looks like it was penned in the '60s, but has modern mechanicals. Essentially, the Speedback, DBA's debut car, is the best of both worlds. We spoke to Brown about his car.

snippet.title: PS Vita 2000 goes lighter and slimmer
snippet.description: The update to Sony's Vita line will be 20 percent lighter and 15 percent thinner than the current console and comes with 1GB of onboard storage.
